blood cortisol decreased AE may indicate that the patient has cushing disease, ectopic cushing syndrome, or a tumor of the adrenal gland that is producing too much cortisol.
a cardiovascular disorder AE that results in easy or excessive bruising and bleeding. The bleeding results from unusually low levels of platelets.
a pain AE that is observed in the bladder, usually a symptom of bladder infection.
an eye AE that results in involuntary, forcible closure of the eyelids.The spasms may leave the eyelids completely closed, causing functional blindness even though the eyes and vision are normal.
an abnormal vision AE which has an outcome of loss of vision in one eye that is not permanent.
a hematology investigation result abnormal AE that results in low blood cortisol levels
blood cortisol decreased AE may indicate that the patient has addison disease, hypopituitarism, suppression of normal pituitary or adrenal function.
a hematology investigation result abnormal AE that results in high blood creatine levels
blood creatine increased AE may indicate that the kidneys are not fucntioning properly
a surgical procedure that replaces missing bone in order to repair bone fractures that are extremely complex, pose a significant health risk to the patient, or fail to heal properly
a hematology investigation result abnormal AE that signifies that a patient is allergic to a particular substance
a hematology investigation result abnormal AE that results in low levels of testosterone which can lead to infertility and a low sex drive

A macrocytic anemia AE is an anemia AE that has an outcome of a macrocytic anemia, which is an anemia (defined as blood with an insufficient concentration of hemoglobin) in which the red blood cells (erythrocytes) are larger than their normal volume.
a bone disorder AE that has an outcome of low bone densityl, but not low enough to be considered osteoporosis

a surgical AE that occurs after a bone graftr procedure, which replaces missing bone in order to repair bone fractures that are extremely complex, pose a significant health risk to the patient, or fail to heal properly.

bone marrow edema AE is an edema AE that occurs when excess fluids in the bone marrow buildup and cause swelling. This condition is often caused by a protective reaction of the body in response to an injury or inflammation
an investigation result abnormal AE that detects areas of increased or decreased bone activity. These may indicate bone injury or disease.
Nervous system AE that covers a variety of conditions that may impair function of the brachial plexus nerve network, most of which are caused by trauma.
a bradycardia AE that results in a disturbance in the heart rhythm in which the heart rate is abnormally slowed.
a bradycardia AE that results in a fetal heart rate of less than 120 beats per minute, generally associatedwith hypoxia
a brain disorder AE  that results in the complete and irreversible loss of brain function
a brain disorder AE  that results in brain tissue, cerebrospinal fluid, and blood vessels being moved or pressed away from their usual position inside the skull.
a brain injury AE,  injury to the brain caused by an external force, that results in a brain AE
a brain mass AE is a mass or growth of abnormal cells in your brain or close to your brain

an imaging investigation result abnormal AE  shows how the brain and its tissues are working. Abnormal results may be due to: Alzheimer’s disease or dementia, brain tumors, epilepsy, and movement disorders.

Eyelid disorder AE is a eye AE that is a condition specifically affects the eyelid. It can include drooping, twitching, inflammation, paralysis, and growths. Occasional fluttering of one eyelid is normal.

Hepatic steatosis AE is a liver disorder AE than popularly called as ‘fatty liver’ is a pathological aspect of liver, whose specific cells (hepatocytes) are filled with lipids (fats). It is a reversible liver disease: ‘is not still very ill, but cries for help’.
An arthropathy AE is a joint pain AE that has an outcome of arthropahty, which is any disorder of the joints.
This is an AE which is an injury to the abdomen and its signs and symptoms include abdominal pain, tenderness, rigidity, and bruising of the external abdomen.

A balantis AE is a reproductive system AE that has an outcome of a balantis, which is an infectious or non-infectious inflammatory process that affects the glans penis. Symptoms include redness and pain of the glans penis and foreskin and discharge.

Pruritus genital AE is a pruritus AE that also called genital itching, Itching in the genital region can result from irritation, allergy, inflammation, infection or cancer. Irritation can occur as a result of exposure to chemicals in soaps, feminine hygiene products, perfumes, lubricants, douches, and creams.

cholecystitis AE is an gallbladder enlargement AE that has an outcome of cholecystitis, which is an acute or chronic inflammation involving the gallbladder wall. It may be associated with the presence of gallstones.
Chromaturia AE is an urine abnormality AE that has an outcome of chromaturia, which is an abnormal coloration of the urine.
Chromosome abnormality AE is a genetic AE that has an outcome of chromsome abnormality which is a missing, extra, or irregular protion of chromosomal DNA.

A coagulopathy AE is a blood disorder AE that has an outcome of coagulopathy, which is a condition in which there is a deviation from or interruption of the normal coagulation properties of the blood.

Combined immunodeficiency AE is an immune system AE that has an outcome of combined immunodeficiency, which represents a group of rare, sometimes fatal, congenital disorders characterized by little or no immune response.
Hepatic enzyme abnormal AE is a liver related investigation result abnormal AE that the lab test result of hepatic enzyme deviates from its normal value.

A coronary artery aneurysm AE is a coronary artery disorder AE that has an outcome of coronary artery aneurysm, which is a coronary dilatation which exceeds the diameter of normal adjacent segments or the diameter of the patient's largest coronary vessel by 1.5 times.
Injection site atrophy AE is an injection-site AE that muscle atrophy occur in the injection site.
A cutaneous tuberculosis AE is a tuberculosis AE that has an outcome of cutaneous tuberculosis, which is an invasion of the skin by Mycobacterium tuberculosis.
Breath sounds abnormal AE is a respiratory system AE that is characterized by abnormal breath sound, it can indicate fluid in the lungs or asthma.
Skin abrasion AE is a skin AE that is a wound caused by superficial damage to the skin, no deeper than the epidermis.

Trigeminal neuralgia AE is a neuralgia AE that is a neuropathic disorder characterized by episodes of intense pain in the face, originating from the trigeminal nerve. The clinical association between TN and hemifacial spasm is the so-called tic douloureux.
Face injury AE is an injury AE that injury occurs in the face.

Muscle contrature AE is a muscle AE that can occur for many reasons, such as paralysis, muscular atrophy, and forms of muscular dystrophy. Fundamentally, the muscle and its tendons shorten, resulting in reduced flexibility.
A palsy AE that has a symmetric limitation of the movements of both eyes in the same direction.

Conjugate gaze palsy AE is a gaze palsy AE that is a disorder affecting the ability to move both eyes in the same direction. These palsies can affect gaze in a horizontal, upward, or downward direction.
Horizontal gaze palsy AE is a gaze palsy AE that is the paresis of conjugate eye movements.

a behavioral and neurological AE that refers to rigid body movements and chronic abnormal positions of the body. This symptom is not the same as showing poor posture or slumping over. Rather, it is often the result of a serious spinal cord or brain injury.
a behavioral and neurological AE that shows the body becomes entire rigid and uncontrolled jerking. They may last mere seconds, or continue for several minutes.
Eyelid ptosis AE is an eye disorder AE that is a drooping or falling of the upper or lower eyelid.
Facial paresis AE is a paresis AE that is a common problem that involves the paralysis of any structures innervated by the facial nerve.
Menstrual disorder AE is an abnormal condition in a woman's menstrual cycle.
